<TEXT>
 A US businessman sentenced <TIMEX2 val="2000-12-06" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">yesterday</TIMEX2> to <TIMEX2 val="P20Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">20 years hard labor</TIMEX2> in Russia is
 waiting to hear if he will be pardoned. Edmund Pope denies spying charges.
 He has written to President Vladimir Putin to request his release. A
 Presidential Pardons Commission will meet <TIMEX2 val="2000-12-08" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">tomorrow</TIMEX2> to consider the request.
 It's expected to recommend granting the pardon. BBC News for The World. I am
 Gregor Cragey.
</TEXT>
